         <notesStmt>
            <note type="summary">1. Z. answers whether to use the kavvanot of the
                            weekdays for Shabbat prayers. 2. Regarding the perimeter around the
                            Torah ark for minḥah and ʿaraṿit prayers. 3. Instructs Rovigo to ask
                            Ifoa? if he requires Sefer ha-Gilgulim. 4. Neḥemias has completed
                            copying Yodei ha-Binah. Z. has paid Neḥemias and Miẓa for their work on
                            Kinuei ha-Shemot on behalf of Rovigo. Neḥemias also begun copyingSefer
                            ha-Kavvanot for Rovigo. 5. Z. is writing an unspecified text for Rovigo.
                            6. Forgives Rovigo for not sending wine despite Z’s wife’s illness? 7.
                            in the post script Z. explains that he gave the letter to R. David
                            Aviater who had to attend to his own affairs and therefore did not send
                            his letter on the usual post day ? (ẓman ketiṿat) –––– Unterschied zw.
                            Kavvanot bei Gebeten an Shabbat u. Wochentagen; bester Zeitpunkt f.
                            Geschlechtsverkehr Mitternacht an Shabbat; an Feiertagen, die auf
                            Shabbat fallen ist im Amidah die Kavvana des Feiertages anzuwenden;
                            Kavvanaot des Tischgebetes am Feiertag; über Musiknoten; Hakafa (rit.
                            Einkreisen) des Torahschreins findet nur zum Morgengebet statt; Nefillat
                            Afim während der Seliḥot zur Wachzeit; Abschreiben von Büchern</note>
            <note type="incipit" xml:lang="he">חבתי בתשלומי כפל
                        אגרותיך</note>
         </notesStmt>
